Question: Java String: split String: :I have this String: String string="NNP,PERSON,true,?,IN,O,false,pobj,NNP,ORGANIZATION,true,?,p";How can I do to split it into an array every 4 commas?I would like something like this:      String[] a=string.split("d{4}");     a[0]="NNP,PERSON,true,?";     a[1]="IN,O,false,pobj";     a[2]="NNP,ORGANIZATION,true,?";     a[3]="p";
Please using this api: StringTokenizer.nextToken.
Answer: <<<api>>>: StringTokenizer
<<<code>>>: 
```java
String string="NNP,PERSON,true,?,IN,O,false,pobj,NNP,ORGANIZATION,true,?,p";
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(string, ",");
ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<String>();
while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
    list.add(st.nextToken());
}
String[] array = new String[list.size() / 4 + (list.size() % 4 == 0 ? 0 : 1)];
for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i += 4) {
    array[i / 4] = String.join(",", list.subList(i, Math.min(i + 4, list.size())));
}
```
<<<explanation>>>: We first create a StringTokenizer to split the string by commas. We then add each token to an ArrayList. We create a new array of Strings with the appropriate size. We then loop through the ArrayList, adding 4 tokens at a time to the array. We use String.join to concatenate the tokens into a single string with commas in between.
```

